        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 4:09PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ayersville, or near Mayodan, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Eden...
Reidsville...
Wentworth...
Mayodan...
Madison...
Stoneville...
and Oregon Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
